Name: Booger
AboutMe:
Google Developer Expert in Android (http://developers.google.com/experts)

Software engineer working and living in the US desert (Arizona). Been developing Enterprise Java for about 15 years, and now developing Android full time for the health care industry.

Android enthusiast, involved in educating people about the platform on many different levels. I organize the local Google Developer Group, speak at Oscon, AnDevCon, and various other conferences. I even wrote a book about the ADT (http://tiny.cc/adte).

I released my app (https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.wolfsoft.dotd) to the Play Store a few years ago, and have had a successful run with it so far (300K+ downloads, and a 4.4 rating).
